pull.title: Reject BIP-0075 (three years inactivity)
pull.body: Per BIP-0002 expiration rules, this can be requested by anybody.

events.body: @justinwnewton @techguy613 @voisine @jmacwhyte Any progress on this? Has it been implemented anywhere?

@luke-jr It is being used by some of Netki's products, one of which is https://github.com/netkicorp/addressimo.

BRD has some internal WIP projects built on it, but since I am no longer at BRD I can not comment on release schedules.
If the above is insufficient to address your concerns, please let me know before any action is taken so we can discuss. Thanks!
This would need 2 implementations. Is there another Netki product we can reference? And/or can BRD comment on the status of using it?

PwC’s Vulcan platform uses BIP 75 on their mobile wallets as well as at their co-signer.  If you’d like I can connect you to the partner at PwC responsible for the platform.

Justin
